<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="41" type="differential diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Differential diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicName class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Brachysiraceae" genus="Brachysira" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Brachysira procera" order="Naviculales" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="procera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Brachysira procera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lange-Bertalot &amp; Gerd Moser is the species which most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. altepetlensis" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="altepetlensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">B. altepetlensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in valve outline but is larger (25-60 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
), wider at valve center (4.5-6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
) and has less striae in 10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(27-30) (
<bibRefCitation author="Lange-Bertalot, H" journalOrPublisher="Botanic Garden and Botanical Musem Berlin-Dahlem, Freie Universitaet Berlin" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" refId="B36" refString="Lange-Bertalot, H, Moser, G, 1994. Brachysira. Monographie der Gattung. Wichtige Indikator-Species fuer das Gewaesser Monitoring und Naviculadicta nov. gen. Ein Loesungsvorschlag zu dem Problem Navicula sensu lato ohne Navicula sensu stricto. Bibliotheca Diatomologica 29. J. Cramer, Berlin-Stuttgart, 1-212." title="Brachysira. Monographie der Gattung. Wichtige Indikator-Species fuer das Gewaesser Monitoring und Naviculadicta nov. gen. Ein Loesungsvorschlag zu dem Problem Navicula sensu lato ohne Navicula sensu stricto. Bibliotheca Diatomologica 29. J. Cramer, Berlin-Stuttgart, 1 - 212." year="1994">Lange-Bertalot and Moser 1994</bibRefCitation>
). The valve outline of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lange-Bertalot" authorityYear="2004" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Brachysiraceae" genus="Brachysira" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Brachysira neglectissima" order="Naviculales" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="neglectissima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Brachysira neglectissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lange-Bertalot also resembles that of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. altepetlensis" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="altepetlensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">B. altepetlensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the valves of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. neglectissima" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="neglectissima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">B. neglectissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are wider (4.3-4.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
), have more striae (36-40), the areolae are arranged in a way that they give the appearance of waves and each single areola is comparatively not as elongated as in 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. altepetlensis" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="altepetlensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">B. altepetlensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lange-Bertalot, H" journalOrPublisher="Botanic Garden and Botanical Musem Berlin-Dahlem, Freie Universitaet Berlin" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" refId="B36" refString="Lange-Bertalot, H, Moser, G, 1994. Brachysira. Monographie der Gattung. Wichtige Indikator-Species fuer das Gewaesser Monitoring und Naviculadicta nov. gen. Ein Loesungsvorschlag zu dem Problem Navicula sensu lato ohne Navicula sensu stricto. Bibliotheca Diatomologica 29. J. Cramer, Berlin-Stuttgart, 1-212." title="Brachysira. Monographie der Gattung. Wichtige Indikator-Species fuer das Gewaesser Monitoring und Naviculadicta nov. gen. Ein Loesungsvorschlag zu dem Problem Navicula sensu lato ohne Navicula sensu stricto. Bibliotheca Diatomologica 29. J. Cramer, Berlin-Stuttgart, 1 - 212." year="1994">Lange-Bertalot and Moser 1994</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Brachysiraceae" genus="Brachysira" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Brachysira guarrerai" order="Naviculales" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="guarrerai">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Brachysira guarrerai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Vouilloud, Sala &amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Núñez-Avellaneda">Nunez-Avellaneda</normalizedToken>
is also similar in valve outline but the valves are wider (5.5-7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
), have less striae (26-32) and lack papillae in the interstriae (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/0269249X.2013.866909" author="Vouilloud, AA" journalOrPublisher="Diatom Research" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" pagination="147 - 163" refId="B75" refString="Vouilloud, AA, Sala, SE, Nunez-Avellaneda, M, Montoya-Moreno, Y, Duque, SR, 2014. Brachysira (Naviculales, Bacillariophyceae) in lowland waters from Colombia. Diatom Research 29 (2): 147 - 163, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/0269249X.2013.866909" title="Brachysira (Naviculales, Bacillariophyceae) in lowland waters from Colombia." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/0269249X.2013.866909" volume="29" year="2014">Vouilloud et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
The valve dimensions as well as the striae density of the new species fall within the range of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H.Lange-Bertalot" authorityYear="1994" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Brachysiraceae" genus="Brachysira" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Brachysira neoexilis" order="Naviculales" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="neoexilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Brachysira neoexilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lange-Bertalot species complex, but the type population of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. neoexilis" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="neoexilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">B. neoexilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has clear capitate apices and the larger specimens have a very slightly triundulate valve margins (
<bibRefCitation author="Lange-Bertalot, H" journalOrPublisher="Botanic Garden and Botanical Musem Berlin-Dahlem, Freie Universitaet Berlin" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" refId="B36" refString="Lange-Bertalot, H, Moser, G, 1994. Brachysira. Monographie der Gattung. Wichtige Indikator-Species fuer das Gewaesser Monitoring und Naviculadicta nov. gen. Ein Loesungsvorschlag zu dem Problem Navicula sensu lato ohne Navicula sensu stricto. Bibliotheca Diatomologica 29. J. Cramer, Berlin-Stuttgart, 1-212." title="Brachysira. Monographie der Gattung. Wichtige Indikator-Species fuer das Gewaesser Monitoring und Naviculadicta nov. gen. Ein Loesungsvorschlag zu dem Problem Navicula sensu lato ohne Navicula sensu stricto. Bibliotheca Diatomologica 29. J. Cramer, Berlin-Stuttgart, 1 - 212." year="1994">Lange-Bertalot and Moser 1994</bibRefCitation>
). All the other populations from 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. neoexilis" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="neoexilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">B. neoexilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex depicted in the original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Lange-Bertalot, H" journalOrPublisher="Botanic Garden and Botanical Musem Berlin-Dahlem, Freie Universitaet Berlin" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" refId="B36" refString="Lange-Bertalot, H, Moser, G, 1994. Brachysira. Monographie der Gattung. Wichtige Indikator-Species fuer das Gewaesser Monitoring und Naviculadicta nov. gen. Ein Loesungsvorschlag zu dem Problem Navicula sensu lato ohne Navicula sensu stricto. Bibliotheca Diatomologica 29. J. Cramer, Berlin-Stuttgart, 1-212." title="Brachysira. Monographie der Gattung. Wichtige Indikator-Species fuer das Gewaesser Monitoring und Naviculadicta nov. gen. Ein Loesungsvorschlag zu dem Problem Navicula sensu lato ohne Navicula sensu stricto. Bibliotheca Diatomologica 29. J. Cramer, Berlin-Stuttgart, 1 - 212." year="1994">Lange-Bertalot and Moser 1994</bibRefCitation>
) have subcapitate to capitate apices, not matching at all the outline of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. altepetlensis" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="altepetlensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">B. altepetlensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The specimens depicted in 
<bibRefCitation author="Rumrich, U" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Applied Phycology" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" refId="B54" refString="Rumrich, U, Lange-Bertalot, H, Rumrich, M, 2000. Diatomeen der Anden. Von Venezuela bis Patagonien/Feuerland. Und zwei weitere Beitraege. Iconographia Diatomologica 9. A.R.G. Gantner Verlag K.G., Ruggell, 1-673." title="Diatomeen der Anden. Von Venezuela bis Patagonien / Feuerland. Und zwei weitere Beitraege. Iconographia Diatomologica 9. A. R. G. Gantner Verlag K. G., Ruggell, 1 - 673." year="2000">Rumrich et al. (2000)</bibRefCitation>
, identified as 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. neoexilis" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="neoexilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">B. neoexilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Pl. 89: figs 18-20), closely resemble 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. altepetlensis" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="altepetlensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">B. altepetlensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in valve outline but they clearly differ from specimens depicted in the type description of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. neoexilis" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="neoexilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">B. neoexilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lange-Bertalot, H" journalOrPublisher="Botanic Garden and Botanical Musem Berlin-Dahlem, Freie Universitaet Berlin" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" refId="B36" refString="Lange-Bertalot, H, Moser, G, 1994. Brachysira. Monographie der Gattung. Wichtige Indikator-Species fuer das Gewaesser Monitoring und Naviculadicta nov. gen. Ein Loesungsvorschlag zu dem Problem Navicula sensu lato ohne Navicula sensu stricto. Bibliotheca Diatomologica 29. J. Cramer, Berlin-Stuttgart, 1-212." title="Brachysira. Monographie der Gattung. Wichtige Indikator-Species fuer das Gewaesser Monitoring und Naviculadicta nov. gen. Ein Loesungsvorschlag zu dem Problem Navicula sensu lato ohne Navicula sensu stricto. Bibliotheca Diatomologica 29. J. Cramer, Berlin-Stuttgart, 1 - 212." year="1994">Lange-Bertalot and Moser 1994</bibRefCitation>
). The specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Brachysiraceae" genus="Brachysira" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Brachysira" order="Naviculales" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Brachysira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found by 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Abarca-Mejía">Abarca-Mejia</normalizedToken>
(2010) in a spring also in the Lerma-Chapala Basin, closely resemble 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. altepetlensis" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="altepetlensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">B. altepetlensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in LM, but her identification was based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Rumrich, U" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Applied Phycology" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" refId="B54" refString="Rumrich, U, Lange-Bertalot, H, Rumrich, M, 2000. Diatomeen der Anden. Von Venezuela bis Patagonien/Feuerland. Und zwei weitere Beitraege. Iconographia Diatomologica 9. A.R.G. Gantner Verlag K.G., Ruggell, 1-673." title="Diatomeen der Anden. Von Venezuela bis Patagonien / Feuerland. Und zwei weitere Beitraege. Iconographia Diatomologica 9. A. R. G. Gantner Verlag K. G., Ruggell, 1 - 673." year="2000">Rumrich et al. (2000)</bibRefCitation>
, which led her to identify those valves as 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. neoexilis" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="neoexilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">B. neoexilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="41" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
this new 
<taxonomicName class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Brachysiraceae" genus="Brachysira" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Brachysira" order="Naviculales" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Brachysira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species takes the name from the word 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“āltepētl”">&quot;altepētl&quot;</normalizedToken>
which means &quot;water mountain&quot; in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Náhuatl">Nahuatl</normalizedToken>
language, that is how the surrounding mountains were used to be named by native people 500 years ago, at the time Spaniards first came to the region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="41" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
apart from the type locality, this species was also found in four streams sampled for this study, namely 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Peña">Pena</normalizedToken>
Colorada (site 4), San 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Martín">Martin</normalizedToken>
(site 5), La Laborcilla 1 (site 7) and La Laborcilla 2 (site 8), all of these sites were characterized by low specific conductivity (≤ 100 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μS">μS</normalizedToken>
/cm) and pH values going from acidic to slightly alcaline (5.1-7.9). But 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. altepetlensis" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="altepetlensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">B. altepetlensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only reached high relative abundances (&gt;10%) in acidic waters (pH= 5.1-5.8) with low specific conductivity (42-53 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μS">μS</normalizedToken>
/cm).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
